<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="586" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1003,1893]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1003,1028]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small black flies, abdomen with very narrow thin whitish band on 
<number box="[1074,1086,1004,1029]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="3.0">3</number>
rd to 
<number box="[1155,1168,1004,1029]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="5.0">5</number>
th tergites; palpus dark brown; gena less than 
<number box="[400,414,1039,1064]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[423,436,1039,1064]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="5.0">5</number>
of eye height; antenna with 
<number box="[753,763,1040,1064]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1.0">1</number>
st flagellomere about 
<number box="[1009,1044,1039,1064]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="2.6">2.6</number>
times as long as pedicel; hind tibia with 
<number box="[208,222,1076,1100]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="2.0">2</number>
preapical dorsal setae; abdominal syntergite 
<number box="[732,742,1076,1100]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[760,776,1076,1100]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="2.0">2</number>
without median marginal setae, no median discal setae on 
<number box="[151,163,1111,1136]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="3.0">3</number>
rd and 
<number box="[243,257,1111,1136]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="4.0">4</number>
th tergites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1003,1893]" box="[199,1436,1148,1173]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586">
<bibRefCitation author="Mesnil" box="[199,358,1148,1173]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" refString="Mesnil, L. P. (1970) Description de nouveaux tachinaires de l'ancien monde, et notes synonymiques (Diptera, Tachinidae). Mushi, 44, 89 - 123." type="journal article" year="1970">
Mesnil (
<number box="[292,350,1148,1172]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1970.0">1970</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described this species in detail from a single female. Here are given some additional characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="586" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1003,1893]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1183,1208]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586">Description.</emphasis>
Female. Vertex about 
<number box="[594,643,1183,1208]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="0.25">0.25</number>
of head width; frontal vitta widened anteriorly, about 
<number box="[1243,1278,1184,1208]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1.4">1.4</number>
times as wide as fronto-orbital plate at middle; parafacial about 
<number box="[707,721,1220,1244]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[731,743,1220,1244]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="3.0">3</number>
as wide as 
<number box="[872,882,1220,1244]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1.0">1</number>
st flagellomere at middle height; gena about 
<number box="[1387,1436,1220,1244]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="0.38">0.38</number>
of eye height; lower margin of face rather weakly warped forward; outer vertical seta fine; ocellar seta fine, subequal in length to outer vertical seta; 
<number box="[606,620,1292,1316]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1.0">1</number>
prevertical and 
<number box="[801,815,1292,1316]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="2.0">2</number>
proclinate orbital setae; lowest frontal seta nearly level with base of pedicel; fronto-orbital plate with rather sparse short black hairs, 
<number box="[1037,1079,1328,1352]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
hairs descending below lowest frontal seta; antenna falling short of lower margin of face by about length of pedicel; antenna with 
<number box="[1255,1265,1364,1388]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1.0">1</number>
st flagellomere about 
<number box="[226,261,1399,1424]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="2.6">2.6</number>
times as long as pedicel; palpus dark brown. Relative lengths of costal sectors 
<number box="[1234,1248,1399,1424]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="2.0">2</number>
nd, 
<number box="[1296,1308,1399,1424]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="3.0">3</number>
rd and 
<number box="[1400,1414,1399,1424]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="4.0">4</number>
th approximately as 
<number box="[354,368,1436,1461]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="3.0">3</number>
: 
<number box="[371,412,1436,1461]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="7.5">7.5</number>
: 
<number box="[416,456,1436,1461]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="3.5">3.5</number>
; vein M from dm-cu crossvein to its bend about 
<number box="[1022,1057,1436,1461]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times distance between the bend and wing margin. Legs black; mid tibia with 
<number box="[664,678,1472,1496]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1.0">1</number>
anterodorsal, 
<number box="[839,853,1472,1496]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="2.0">2</number>
posterodorsal and 
<number box="[1069,1083,1472,1496]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1.0">1</number>
ventral setae; hind tibia with 
<number box="[1422,1436,1472,1496]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="2.0">2</number>
preapical dorsal setae; claws and pulvilli slightly shorter than 
<number box="[847,859,1508,1533]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="5.0">5</number>
th tarsomere. Abdomen black in ground color, with thin grayish pruinosity on anterior portion of each tergite, shining black on major portion of 
<number box="[1209,1223,1543,1568]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="4.0">4</number>
th and 
<number box="[1302,1315,1543,1568]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="5.0">5</number>
th tergites; syntergite 
<number box="[268,278,1580,1604]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[296,312,1580,1604]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="2.0">2</number>
without median marginal setae; 
<number box="[680,692,1580,1605]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="3.0">3</number>
rd tergite with one pair of median marginal setae which is slightly inserted anteriorly; 
<number box="[370,384,1615,1640]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="4.0">4</number>
th and 
<number box="[460,473,1615,1640]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="5.0">5</number>
th tergites each with a row of marginal setae, without distinct discal setae. Body length: 
<quantity box="[303,371,1653,1676]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1003,1893]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586">
