<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="586" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1003,1893]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1796,1820]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is distinct among members of this genus in lacking the median marginal setae on the abdominal syntergite 
<number box="[400,410,1832,1856]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[428,444,1832,1856]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="2.0">2</number>
and median discal setae on 
<number box="[780,792,1831,1856]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="3.0">3</number>
rd and 
<number box="[879,893,1831,1856]" pageId="10" pageNumber="586" value="4.0">4</number>
th tergites, and having a broadly shining black abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
